  "prompt": "Does carnotaurus have slitted eyes pupils too or doesn't?",
  "response": "Carnotaurus, like most theropod dinosaurs, is believed to have had round pupils rather than slitted eyes. The evidence for the shape of dinosaur pupils comes mainly from studies of their closest living relatives\u2014birds and reptiles. Most birds, which are directly descended from theropod dinosaurs like Carnotaurus, typically have round pupils. Similarly, many reptiles also have round pupils, though some, like certain lizards and snakes, have vertical or horizontal slits.\n\nThere is no direct fossil evidence for the exact shape of Carnotaurus's pupils, but based on its phylogenetic relationships and the characteristics of modern relatives, it is more likely that Carnotaurus had round pupils rather than slitted ones.",
